<br>
Im my arrogance I returned to the warrens two nights later convinced I could go it alone.<br>
<br>
So - how did I fare?..<br>
<br>
Well - I didn't even get past the door - I had forgoten that the last time I had been there I had been made invisible by a caster in the group and as I breezed past the guard on the city gates I was almost instantly slaughtered...<br>
<br>
...and woke up Nekkid in Northern Karana. Imagine the terror of the long walk back to Tox and the warrens Armourless and Weaponless - only to have to try and slip the guard in Paniell again - I was dreading it.<br>
<br>
When suddenly who should come into view but Niil, the halfling Druid.<br>
<br>
Not only did Niil teleport me to Tox free of charge but then proceeded to SOW me and provide me with a greater camoflage spell - this enabled me to slip the guard, retrieve my corpse and get into the warrens. <br>
<br>
About five minutes after I was safely (ha ha) tucked away in the Warrens I got a tell from Niil asking if I had been successful.<br>
<br>
Niil got nothing from me and asked nothing of me. It was a genuinely selfless act. Once I have left the warrens I intend to gift him something to show my appreciation. <br>
<br>
If you see Niil thank him and show him kindness.<br>
<br>
I also noted that we was guildless and he is exactly the calibre of individual we look for in a Victus member. <p>Tassius Ghoulwrecker

